;; Intelligent Model Selection

{:title "Intelligent Model Selection Based on Task Characteristics"
 :version "1.0.0"
 :type :enhancement
 :priority :high

 :description
 "Automatically select the optimal model (Opus 4.6, Sonnet 4.5, Haiku 4.5, etc.)
  based on task characteristics, agent type, and workflow phase. Different tasks
  need different capabilities - complex reasoning requires Opus, execution uses
  Sonnet, simple tasks use Haiku. Make this selection automatic and intelligent."

 :motivation
 {:user-quote "The workflow should default to having agent backends automatically
               chosen for the task (for example, Opus 4.6 for thinking tasks,
               Sonnet 4.5 for most execution tasks, Haiku for simple ones)"

  :current-problem
  ["Backend is selected globally (Claude, Codex, etc.)"
   "Model is fixed per backend configuration"
   "No automatic model selection based on task type"
   "Opus used for everything (expensive, slow)"
   "Or Sonnet used for everything (not optimal for complex reasoning)"
   "No capability metadata for models"]

  :desired-behavior
  ["Opus 4.6 for complex reasoning, planning, architecture decisions"
   "Sonnet 4.5 for most code generation, implementation, review"
   "Haiku 4.5 for simple tasks, validation, formatting"
   "Automatic selection based on task characteristics"
   "Cost optimization without sacrificing quality"
   "Workflow phases can specify model requirements"]}

